notesStmt.note: Several larger lacunae. The first quire is lost and the last quire is imperfect.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The Hagiographa, provided with vowel-points and accents, masorah magna and parva.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 24 26; written lines: 24 26; Uniform layout. Masorah magna in one line in the upper and up to four lines in the lower margin. In the resteored part of the manuscript there is no masorah. The number of verses and siman stated at the end of each book, except of Chronicles. The beginning of sedarim indicated in the margin with an ornamental samekh. Visible mastara ruling.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite square script, punctuated, of 16th century.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 23 July 1881, folio [155v].
